2727.name: weather_radar_platform
2727.docs:
Weather radar data processing platform library

This platform provides a comprehensive system for processing and analyzing weather radar data
with AI-powered analysis capabilities. The system consists of several key components:

## Core Components

- **API Server**: REST API with public read access and authenticated management endpoints ([`api`])
- **NWS Integration**: Background polling of National Weather Service text products ([`weather`])
- **Analysis Engine**: AI-powered weather analysis using Claude AI with intelligent caching ([`analysis`])
- **Event System**: In-process event coordination using tokio broadcast channels ([`core`])
- **Authentication**: JWT authentication system with admin token exchange ([`auth`])
- **Rate Limiting**: Selective rate limiting infrastructure ([`rate_limit`], [`middleware`])

## Architecture

The platform uses Redis for caching and coordination, JWT authentication for security,
and an event-driven architecture for real-time analysis generation. All public APIs
serve pre-cached data for optimal performance.
